tt0110781/ IMDb lists release date as: 21 October 1994 -->\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Partners''\n| Doctor\n| [[Short film|Short]] film<br />Nominated &ndash; [[Academy Award for Best Live Action Short Film]]\n|-\n| 1994\n! scope=\"row\" | [[The Substitute Wife (1994 film)|''The Substitute Wife'']]\n| Martin Hightower\n|\n|-\n| 1994\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Lakota Woman: Siege at Wounded Knee]]''\n| Uncredited\n|\n|-\n| 1995\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Present Tense, Past Perfect''\n| Charles\n|\n|-\n| 1997\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[End of Summer (1995 film)|End of Summer]]''\n| Theo Remmington\n|\n|-\n| 1997\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Gold Coast''\n| align=\"center\" | \u2014\n| Director and executive producer\n|-\n| 1998\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Tower of the Firstborn]]''\n| John Shannon\n|\n|-\n| 2000\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Dark Prince: The True Story of Dracula]]''\n| Father Stefan\n|\n|-\n| 2005\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[The Poseidon Adventure (2005 film)|The Poseidon Adventure]]''\n| Captain Paul Gallico\n|\n|}\n\n===Television series===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\"\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" | Role(s)\n! scope=\"col\" | Channel\n! scope=\"col\" class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 1977\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Lou Grant (TV series)|Lou Grant]]''\n| Donald Stryker\n| [[CBS]]\n| Episode: \"Nazi\"\n|-\n| 1995\u20131996\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Homicide: Life on the Street]]''\n| align=\"center\" | \u2014\n| [[NBC]]\n| Director<br />Episodes: \"Hate Crimes\"<br>\"White Lies\"\n|-\n| 1997\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Michael Hayes (TV series)|Michael Hayes]]''\n| align=\"center\"| \u2014\n| [[CBS]]\n| Director<br />Episode: \"The Doctor's Tale\"\n|-\n| align=\"center\"| 2002\u20132003\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Odyssey 5]]''\n| Chuck Taggart\n| [[Space (Canadian TV channel)|Space]] <!-- This TV show was made in Canada -->\n| 19 (20) episodes\n|-\n| 2005\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Star Trek: Enterprise]]''\n| John Frederick Paxton\n| [[UPN]]\n| Episodes: