]]\"\n}}\n|-\n| 2005-2007\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Engineering an Empire]]''\n| align=\"center\"| -\n| [[History Channel]]\n| Host (14 episodes)\n|-\n| 2006\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Monk (TV series)|Monk]]''\n| align=\"center\"| \u2013\n| [[USA Network]]\n| Director<br />Episode: \"Mr. Monk, Private Eye\"\n|-\n| 2006\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Monk''\n| Actor playing Stottlemeyer \n| USA Network\n| Episode: \"Mr. Monk and the Actor\"\n|-\n| 2006\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[24 (TV series)|24]]''\n| Christopher Henderson\n| [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]]\n| 11 episodes\n|-\n| 2007\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Las Vegas (TV series)|Las Vegas]]''\n| align=\"center\"| \u2014\n| [[NBC]]\n| Director<br />Episode: \"A Cannon Carol\"\n|-\n| 2010\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Fringe (TV series)|Fringe]]''\n| Scientist Alistair Peck\n| Fox\n| Episode: \"[[White Tulip]]\"\n|-\n| 2010\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Psych (TV series)|Psych]]''\n| Mr. Yin\n| USA Network\n| Episode: \"[[Yang 3 in 2D]]\"\n|-\n| 2010\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Dexter (TV series)|Dexter]]''\n| Stan Liddy\n| [[Showtime (TV network)|Showtime]]\n| 8 episodes\n|-\n| 2013\u20132014\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Sons of Anarchy]]''\n| Charles Barosky\n| [[FX (TV channel)|FX]]\n| 10 episodes\n|-\n| 2012\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[House (TV series)|House]]''\n| Dr. Penza\n| Fox\n| Episode: \"[[Post Mortem (House)|Post Mortem]]\"<br />Also director\n|-\n| 2012\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[The Mob Doctor]]''\n| align=\"center\"| \u2014\n| Fox\n| Director<br />Episode: \"Confessions\"\n|-\n| 2012\u20132017\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Longmire (TV series)|Longmire]]''\n| Lucian Connally\n| [[A&E (TV channel)|A&E]]<br />[[Netflix]]\n| Also director <!-- of those 4 episodes --><br />4 episodes\n|-\n| 2013\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Hawaii Five-0 (2010 TV series)|Hawaii Five-0]]''\n| Curt Stoner\n| CBS\n| Episode: \"Hookman\"\n|-\n| 2013\u20132018\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Hawaii Five-0''\n| align=\"center\" | \u2014\n| CBS\n| Director<br />10 episodes\n|-\n| 2014\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[The Strain (TV series)|The Strain]]''\n| align=\"center\"| \u2014\n| FX\n| Director<br />3 episodes\n|-\n| 2014\u20132015\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Under the Dome (TV series)|Under the Dome]]''\n| align=\"center\"| \u2014\n| CBS\n| Director<br />Episode: \"The Red Door\" (2014)<br />Episode: \"But I'm Not\" (2015)\n|-\n| 2015\u20132017\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[The Last Ship (TV series)|The Last Ship]]''\n| align=\"center\" | \u2014\n| TNT\n| 5 episodes as director<br />Recurring role in season 4\n|-\n| 2015\u20132016\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Tyrant (TV series)|Tyrant]]''\n| align=\"center\" | \u2014\n| FX\n| Director<br />Episode: \"Zanjir\"<br />Episode: \"Bedfellows\"<br />Episode: \"How to Live\"\n|-\n| 2015\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Sleepy Hollow (TV series)|Sleepy Hollow]]''\n| align=\"center\" | \u2014\n| Fox\n| Director<br />Episode: \"I, Witness\"\n|-\n| 2015\u20132016\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Salem (TV series)|Salem]]''\n| align=\"center\" | \u2014\n| WGN America\n| Director<br />Episode: \"The Dark Wine Sea\"<br />Episode: \"Wednesday's Child\"\n|-\n| 2016\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Rush Hour (U.S. TV series)|Rush Hour]]''\n| align=\"center\" | \u2014\n| CBS\n| Director<br />Episode: \"Two Days or The Number of Hours Within the Time Frame\"\n|-\n| 2016\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Outsiders (TV series)|Outsiders]]''\n| align=\"center\" | \u2014\n| WGN America\n| Director<br />Episode: \"Long Live the Bre'lin\"\n|-\n| 2016\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Game of Silence (U.S. TV series)|Game of Silence]]''\n| align=\"center\" | \u2014\n| NBC\n| Director<br />Episode: \"Road Trip\"\n|-\n| 2017\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Shades of Blue (TV series)|Shades of Blue]]''\n| align=\"center\" | \u2014\n| NBC\n| Director<br />Episode: \"Fracture\"<br />Episode: \"House Divided\"\n|-\n| 2018\u20132020\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[MacGyver (2016 TV series)|MacGyver]]''\n| align=\"center\" | Elliot Mason\n| CBS\n| Director \u2014 2 episodes<br>Actor \u2014 2 episodes\n|-\n| 2018\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Mr. Mercedes (TV series)|Mr. Mercedes]]''\n| align=\"center\" | \u2014\n| [[Audience (TV network)|Audience]]\n| Director<br />Episode: \"Andale\"\n|-\n| 2018-19\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Mayans MC]]''\n| align=\"center\" | \u2014\n| FX\n| Director<br />Episode: \"Rata/Ch'o\"<br />Episode: \"Tohil\"\n|-\n| 2018-19\n! scope=\"row\" | ''[[Magnum P.I. (2018 TV series)|Magnum P.I.]]''\n| align=\"center\" | \u2014\n| CBS\n| Director<br />Episode: \"Die He Said\"<br />Episode: \"Blood Brothers\"\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|693}}\n* {{IBDB name}}\n* {{iobdb name|17467}}\n* {{Tcmdb name}}\n* {{amg name|id=75401}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20090429205940/http://www.history.com/engineeringanempire History Channel's ''Engineering an Empire'' site]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20060702000911/http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/story/342880p-292761c.html \"RoboCop in Rome!\"] ''New York Daily News''\n* [https://www.wired.com/wired/archive/15.02/posts.html \"RoboCop, PhD\"] ''Wired News''\n* [http://www.funnyordie.com/videos/521706ecf7/robocop-speaks-to-detroit \"RoboCop speaks to Detroit\"] ''Funny Or Die''\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Weller, Peter}}\n[[Category:1947 births]]\n[[Category:Male actors from Wisconsin]]\n[[Category:Alamo Heights High School alumni]]\n[[Category:American Academy of Dramatic Arts alumni]]\n[[Category:American male film actors]]\n[[Category:American male television actors]]\n[[Category:American television directors]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Military brats]]\n[[Category:Male actors from San Antonio]]\n[[Category:People from Stevens Point, Wisconsin]]\n[[Category:Syracuse University alumni]]\n[[Category:University of North Texas alumni]]\n[[Category:20th-century American male actors]]\n[[Category:21st-century American male actors]]\n[[Category:University of California, Los Angeles alumni]]\n", "name_user": "DodgeBoy102", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikip